    public static enum UnitP.ErrorTypes

    Contains all the supported error types.

    • Enum Constant Detail

      • None

        public static final UnitP.ErrorTypes None
        No error.

      • InvalidOperation

        public static final UnitP.ErrorTypes InvalidOperation
        Associated with invalid operations between UnitP variables not provoked by numeric errors. Examples: addition of UnitP variables with different types; multiplication of UnitP variables outputting an unsupported unit.

      • InvalidUnit

        public static final UnitP.ErrorTypes InvalidUnit
        Associated with faulty instantiations of UnitP variables. Examples: relying on an unsupported input string; including prefixes not supported in that specific context.

      • NumericError

        public static final UnitP.ErrorTypes NumericError
        Associated with invalid operations provoked by numeric overflow or arithmetic errors. Examples: multiplication of too big values; division by zero.

      • NumericParsingError

        public static final UnitP.ErrorTypes NumericParsingError
        Associated with errors triggered when parsing numeric inputs. Example: new UnitP("no-number unit") rather than new UnitP("number unit").

      • InvalidUnitConversion

        public static final UnitP.ErrorTypes InvalidUnitConversion
        Associated with invalid or unsupported conversions. Example: UnitP("1 m/s").ConvertCurrentUnitTo("m/s2").
